    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cylindrical baskets used by Hupa Native North Americans in the Jump Dance ceremony (Xay-ch´idilye). Generally made of plant fibers such as maidenhair fern and spruce, formed into a long, cylindrical shape. </Note_Text>
